.Dd April 22, 2026
.Dt TANGHULU 1
.Os "tanghulu 0.1.0"
.Sh NAME
.Nm tanghulu
.Nd run a string of timed focus/rest sessions
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Cm help
.br
.Nm
.Ar block
.br
.Nm
.Ar name
.br
.Nm
.Cm add Ar name block
.br
.Nm
.Cm redefine Ar name block
.br
.Nm
.Cm rename Ar old new
.br
.Nm
.Cm delete Ar name
.br
.Nm
.Cm list Op Fl v
.br
.Nm
.Cm config Op Cm sound Bro Cm on | Cm off Brc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
runs a sequence of timed segments back to back.
At each transition it prints a message to the terminal,
shows a macOS pop-up dialog, and plays an optional chime.
.Pp
It is named for
.Em 糖葫芦
.Pq tanghulu ,
a Chinese snack of candied hawthorn fruits threaded on a bamboo stick
— segments of sweetness strung together, one after another.
.Pp
A
.Ar block
is a compact expression that describes the sequence of timed segments to run.
Blocks can be typed inline as an argument or saved under a name for reuse.
.Ss Block grammar
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ar N
A segment of
.Ar N
minutes with no label.
.It Ar N Ns = Ns Ar LABEL
A segment of
.Ar N
minutes labeled
.Ar LABEL .
The label appears in the countdown header, the transition message,
and the Ctrl-C breakdown.
.It KxITEM
Repeat
.Ar ITEM
.Ar K
times.
.Ar ITEM
may be a segment, a group, or a named reference.
.It /ITEM,ITEM,.../
A group — multiple items treated as a unit for repetition.
For example,
.Ql 4x/25=focus,5=break/
repeats the focus/break pair four times.
.It Ar NAME
A reference to a saved block.
References are
.Em late-bound :
the saved definition is read at run time, so editing a block with
.Cm redefine
takes effect the next time any block that references it runs.
.It ITEM,ITEM,...
A sequence: items separated by commas run one after another.
.El
.Pp
.Ar N
and
.Ar K
are positive integers.
.Ar LABEL
and
.Ar NAME
must match
.Ql [A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_-]*
and must not be reserved keywords
.Pq see
.Sx SUBCOMMANDS .
.Ss Subcommands
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ar block
Parse
.Ar block
and run it immediately as an ad-hoc session.
.It Ar name
Look up the saved block
.Ar name
and run it.
Equivalent to typing the block expression directly.
.It Cm add Ar name block
Save
.Ar block
under
.Ar name .
Fails if a block with that name already exists; use
.Cm redefine
to overwrite.
The block is validated before saving.
.It Cm redefine Ar name block
Replace the definition of an existing named block.
.It Cm rename Ar old new
Rename a saved block from
.Ar old
to
.Ar new .
.It Cm delete Ar name
Remove a saved block.
.It Cm list Op Fl v
List all saved block names, one per line.
With
.Fl v ,
also print each block's definition.
.It Cm config Op Cm sound Bro Cm on | Cm off Brc
With no arguments, print the current configuration.
With
.Cm sound on
or
.Cm sound off ,
enable or disable the transition chime.
The chime is on by default.
.It Cm help
Show this man page.
Falls back to a synopsis if the man page is not installed.
.El
.Sh RUNTIME BEHAVIOUR
When a block is running,
.Nm
displays a live countdown on a single terminal line that updates every second:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
[focus] 24:37 remaining...
.Ed
.Pp
At the end of each segment it clears the countdown and prints
a transition message:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
25m of focus finished. 5m of break begins.
.Ed
.Pp
It also raises a macOS System Events dialog with the same message
.Pq fire-and-forget; does not block the countdown
and plays
.Pa /System/Library/Sounds/Glass.aiff
if the chime is enabled.
.Pp
Pressing
.Sy Ctrl-C
at any point stops the session and prints a summary:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
tanghulu: stopped at segment 2 of 8; 30m 12s elapsed total
by label:
  focus: 25m 0s
  break: 5m 12s
.Ed
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for configuration and saved blocks.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.config .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Pa ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/tanghulu/blocks/<name>.block
One file per saved block.
Plain text: a header comment followed by the block expression on one line.
.It Pa ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/tanghulu/config
Key=value configuration file.
Currently supports one key:
.Cm sound
.Pq Ql on No or Ql off , default Ql on .
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It 0
No error.
.It 1
Usage or runtime error
.Pq bad block expression, unknown name, etc. .
.It 130
Interrupted by
.Sy Ctrl-C .
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Run three unlabeled segments back to back:
.Dl $ tanghulu 1,3,5
.Pp
One Pomodoro cycle — 25 minutes of focus followed by a 5-minute break:
.Dl $ tanghulu 25=focus,5=break
.Pp
Four Pomodoro cycles in a row:
.Dl $ tanghulu 4x/25=focus,5=break/
.Pp
Save a named block and run it by name:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ tanghulu add pomodoro '4x/25=focus,5=break/'
$ tanghulu pomodoro
.Ed
.Pp
Compose named blocks with inline expressions:
.Dl $ tanghulu 2xpomodoro,15=long_break
.Pp
See all saved blocks with their definitions:
.Dl $ tanghulu list -v
.Pp
Turn off the chime:
.Dl $ tanghulu config sound off
